{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":204437,"duration_api_ms":204153,"num_turns":24,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"43c92024-c366-4569-8e60-4f3f0ec931e6","total_cost_usd":1.0168879999999998,"usage":{"input_tokens":18,"cache_creation_input_tokens":60072,"cache_read_input_tokens":842046,"output_tokens":8813,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":60072,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":18,"outputTokens":8813,"cacheReadInputTokens":842046,"cacheCreationInputTokens":60072,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":1.0168879999999998,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"amendments":[{"body":"MilestoneId::new() in model.rs should reject dot-prefixed names (e.g., `.locks`, `.hidden`) to prevent collision with the new MILESTONE_LOCKS_DIR (`.locks`) directory. Currently, creating a milestone with id `.locks` would place its data directory at `milestones/.locks/`, which is the same path used for lock files of all other milestones. Add a validation rule like `normalized.starts_with('.')` to the existing rejection checks in MilestoneId::new().","rationale":"The new `.locks` directory lives as a sibling to milestone data directories under `milestones/`. Since MilestoneId validation doesn't reject dot-prefixed strings, a milestone named `.locks` would have its data directory collide with the shared lock directory, causing lock files for other milestones (e.g., `milestones/.locks/foo/mutation.lock`) to appear as subdirectories of the `.locks` milestone's data. While unlikely in practice, it's a correctness gap introduced by choosing a dot-prefixed reserved directory name without reserving that namespace in the ID validator."}],"summary":"The diff contains three well-motivated changes: (1) lock files moved to a separate `.locks` directory so that acquiring a lock for a non-existent milestone no longer creates the milestone's data directory as a side-effect (fixing the \"failed operation blocks future create\" class of bugs), (2) read-before-write reordering in `persist_plan` and `update_task_run` so that snapshot reads fail fast before mutating lineage or plan files, and (3) a new `fail_superseded_running_attempt` mechanism that auto-fails stale runless Running entries when a new retry arrives with a different `started_at`. All 102 tests pass. The implementation is correct — the `fail_superseded_running_attempt` function correctly matches raw entries against collapsed-view references via `same_attempt`, the in-memory mutations are persisted via the subsequent `write_task_runs`, and the new tests cover the full lifecycle including completion after auto-fail. The one structural concern is that `MilestoneId` validation doesn't prevent dot-prefixed names, which could collide with the new `.locks` reserved directory."},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"1ed9c7c2-f1f0-4fb8-bd78-1dacd3352c86"}
